2. MODULE 1 — PRISM FILTER

(your “white light → separated components” idea)

Purpose

Break messy input into structured components

Output format

{
  "intent": "",
  "domain": "",
  "action_type": "",
  "leverage_type": "",
  "constraints": [],
  "unknowns": []
}

Starter code (Python)

def prism_filter(text):
    return {
        "intent": text[:120],
        "domain": "unknown",
        "action_type": "explore",
        "leverage_type": "unknown",
        "constraints": [],
        "unknowns": []
    }

👉 Later we plug AI here for real parsing.

⸻

3. MODULE 2 — REFINERY ENGINE

(turn crude → usable fuel)

Purpose

Score signal vs noise and identify value

def refinery(signal):
    score = 0

    if len(signal["intent"]) > 20:
        score += 1
    if signal["action_type"] != "unknown":
        score += 1

    return {
        "score": score,
        "priority": "high" if score > 1 else "low"
    }

👉 This becomes your Hound.HLL / scoring layer later

⸻

4. MODULE 3 — ACTION ENGINE

(idea → execution path)

Purpose

Turn structure into something usable

def action_engine(signal, score):
    if score["priority"] == "high":
        return {
            "type": "build",
            "next_step": "convert into tool or script"
        }
    else:
        return {
            "type": "explore",
            "next_step": "refine idea"
        }


⸻

5. MODULE 4 — INTERFACE (CLI for now)

def run_pipeline(text):
    p = prism_filter(text)
    r = refinery(p)
    a = action_engine(p, r)

    return {
        "prism": p,
        "refinery": r,
        "action": a
    }

if __name__ == "__main__":
    user_input = input("Enter idea: ")
    result = run_pipeline(user_input)
    print(result)


